{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they both felt guilty, because when we were in that little enclave, they walked out with papers and left their children hidden, and they never saw their children again.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were both overcome with guilt, which created a very strong bond between them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, in training to become a nurse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I gave injections, and I learned whatever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was such a believer in education that-- under the worst possible circumstances.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think this is very good because it makes your life a little more normal when you try to think about other things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, I learned English in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For a piece of bread, we bought a copy of And we had a friend in the camp who spoke English, and he taught me English using I had a very Southern point of view on the Civil War at the time.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but surprisingly enough, when the war ended, I could speak English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In the-- in the camp, the days were, for us, were really monotonous.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In the morning, we lived on berths, very crowded, in one large room, maybe 100 or 150 people in one large room.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the morning, my father would come, and I-- I was always on the top berth-- there were three levels-- because I was young.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I could climb.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He would come, and I would shake out my straw pillow and my blanket to throw out the mice that literally bred in my bed, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I have a horror of rodents ever since then, understandably.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then we would have something to eat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then they would-- I would do the rounds with my father in the morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
